						<summary>

						<p>On the wall of the Irukulamma temple.</p>						

						<p>Vīra-Sāvaṇṇa-Voḍeya, 1364 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Dated in Śaka 1286, <hi rend="italic">Krōdhi, Mārgaśira,</hi> ba. 5, Friday, corresponding to 1364 A.D., December 13.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Records the decision of the <hi rend="italic">nānādēśīs</hi> who seem to have granted certain levies collected at the Friday-market established by Kāchaṇṇa of Nellore, to the goddess [Eraku]lāparamēśvarī.</p>						

						<p>(Published in <hi rend="italic">Inscriptions of the Nellore District,</hi> Part II, No. 78, p. 848).</p>						

						</summary>
